{
  "texts": [
    "An ICO whitepaper, perceived as a prospectus for an initial public offering (IPO) in a less regulated way, provides information that can impact investors' decisions and, to some extent, determine the success of projects.",
    "Many dimensions of such texts influence the performance of ICO.",
    "For instance, ICO projects with higher technological sophistication shown in whitepapers are more likely to be successful and less likely to be delisted (Liu et al. 2021).",
    "Those whitepapers that are unique-that is, have more project-specific information and avoid borrowing common phrases from previous whitepapers-can lead to higher fundraising amounts and better post-ICO performance (Yen and Wang 2021; Florysiak and Schandlbauer 2022).",
    "The readability and sentiment expressed in whitepapers can also affect investors' decisions to invest in the described project (Stanley 2019; Sapkota and Grobys 2021)."
  ]
}